  {"course":"yolo_coding","question":"In Python YOLO pipelines, why convert tensors to native types before JSON serialization?","answer":"Because JSON cannot serialize tensors; convert to float/int/list first.","reasoning":"API responses require primitives. Use .tolist(), float(), int() before json.dumps()."},
  {"course":"yolo_coding","question":"How do you convert a YOLO box tensor b.xyxy0] into four Python floats?","answer":"Use x1,y1,x2,y2 = b.xyxy0].tolist().","reasoning":"tolist() converts a 1D tensor to a Python list of numbers."},
  {"course":"yolo_coding","question":"What does the xyxy bounding box format represent?","answer":"Top-left (x1,y1) and bottom-right (x2,y2) corners.","reasoning":"Corner coordinates are convenient for IoU and NMS computations."},
  {"course":"yolo_coding","question":"What does the xywh bounding box format represent?","answer":"Top-left (x,y) plus width (w) and height (h).","reasoning":"Many UI overlays prefer width/height for drawing rectangles."},
  {"course":"yolo_coding","question":"How do you convert xyxy to xywh in Python?","answer":"x=x1; y=y1; w=x2-x1; h=y2-y1.","reasoning":"Width and height are differences between opposing corners."},
  {"course":"yolo_coding","question":"How do you convert xywh to xyxy in Python?","answer":"x1=x; y1=y; x2=x+w; y2=y+h.","reasoning":"Bottom-right corner is offset by width/height."},
